# Mini Demo Components

Applies when creating or editing animated mini demo components on the marketing site.

Read `docs/mini_demos.md` for the complete specification before writing any demo code.

## Architecture (enforced)

1. Every demo lives in `src/site/components/<feature>-demo/` with a barrel `index.ts`.
2. Animation uses `useSequence` from `src/site/components/app-demo/useSequence.ts` — never write custom timer logic.
3. Step types (`Step`) come from `src/site/components/app-demo/types.ts`.
4. All timing and static data live in `data.ts` — components only receive props.
5. The orchestrator (`<Feature>Demo.tsx`) is a thin wiring layer: derives booleans from sequence state, passes down as props.
6. Sub-components get their own files, named for their role in the feature narrative (e.g. `RepoConnector.tsx`, not `DemoSidebar.tsx`).

## Animation Timing

- Steps use **relative delays** (ms before firing), not absolute timestamps.
- Standard ranges: reveals 400–800ms, actions 600–1000ms, fetches 1200–1600ms, reading pauses 1600–2500ms, reset 2000–3000ms.
- Total loop: 12–18 seconds.
- CSS transitions: `duration-300` (micro), `duration-500` (standard), `duration-700` (major).

## Visual Fidelity

- Demos must visually replicate the real app — same tokens, same layout proportions, same interaction patterns.
- All colors, weights, radii, shadows, and borders from `src/styles/theme.css` tokens.
- Demo-scale text: `text-[9px]` titles, `text-[8px]` body, `text-[7px]` metadata, `text-[6px]` micro labels.
- No placeholder content — all text must be realistic and meaningful.

## Forbidden

- Generic component names (`DemoSidebar`, `DemoCard`, `DemoPanel`)
- Inline timer logic or `useEffect` with `setTimeout` in component files
- Hardcoded colors, font weights, or border radii
- Lorem ipsum or meaningless placeholder text
- Duplicating the `useSequence` hook (import the shared one)
